Herbaceous species do not "climatically" compete with shrubs and trees (p.14), e.g., plants cannot compete for climate.
If what the author meant was that, because of the climatic conditions at the time Europeans arrived in the Intermountain Region, shrubs and Juniperus were at a competitive disadvantage, he/she needs to support that opinion (and others on this page) from the scientific literature.
These generalized statements are much too broad to be supported by a single citation.
