Environmental conditions in the Intermountain Region considerably different today than they were when the mega -fauna was a functional part of the environment of the Intermountain Region.
Introducing alien cattle and horses was not "simply filling the vacant large herbivore niche" (p.20).
And, it is biologically impossible for livestock to "represent a potentially functional replacement for the mega -fauna" (p.19).
Livestock are not, functionally or otherwise, "surrogate13 herbivores", "surrogate grazers", or "surrogate mega fauna" (pp.19,23,24).
